subSubSection.paragraph:
Johnston’s Wildebeest (
C. johnstoni
), the Eastern White-bearded Wildebeest (
C. albojubatus
), and the Serengeti Whitebearded Wildebeest (
C. mearnsi
) have usually been considered to be subspecies of 
C. taurinus
, but they are consistently different in external appearance, in measurements, and in mtDNA. This species is considered monotypic here.
